import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between population and number of engineers?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['engineers'], bins=10, color='green', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Engineers')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['engineers'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    hurricanes_by_state = data.groupby('state')['hurricanes'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(hurricanes_by_state.index, hurricanes_by_state.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    ax.axhline(y=hurricanes_by_state.max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {hurricanes_by_state.max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
